{"TopicId":170996,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Starlink Thread (split from SpaceX)","CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-17T03:46:55Z","PageNum":2,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-03T17:29:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223666239\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159887\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567531682\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly. They carry onboard fuel to adjust trajectory and stay in space, and enough to perform a rapid deorbit if there was a problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, 12 000 sats raising risk of collision up to percents per year are always in orbit.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf one dies and deorbits, they launch a replacement to keep the cloud same dangerous.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Technical Ben","CreatedById":10512,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-03T17:29:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223666237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159887\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567531610\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd as the 12 000 objects constellation is presumed to be permanently existing, the argument of orbit decay is not applicable.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis cloud of floating contact mines will be existing and make low orbits as dangerous as a minefield.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust like all those cars, boats and aircraft... oh wait!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-03T17:30:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223666243\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159887\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567531786\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210512\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Technical Ben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Technical Ben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust like all those cars, boats and aircraft... oh wait!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCars, boats, and aircrafts can maneuver and stop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf 12 000 sats start maneuvering in evasive action, the chaos just gets absolutely chaotic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-03T17:31:36Z\u0022 title=\u002209/03/2019 05:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 3, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Technical Ben","CreatedById":10512,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-03T17:31:48Z","Content":"\n\u0